article.headline: Kirkwood scores 28, leads Harvard over Columbia 91-82

images.name: Second Half Spurt Leads Harvard Past Columbia  - Via Ivy League
images.caption: Noah Kirkwood tied his career-high with 28 points to help Harvard past Columbia

article.linkText: Kirkwood scores 28, leads Harvard over Columbia 91-82
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Noah Kirkwood scored 28 points, tying his career high, and Harvard defeated Columbia 91-82 on Saturday. Luka Sakota added 18 points, Kale Catchings 14 and Louis Lemond 10 for the Crimson (9-5, 1-1 Ivy League). Cameron Shockley-Okeke scored 19 points with 11 rebounds for the Lions (4-11, 1-3). Geronimo Rubio De La Rosa added 16 points, Eddie Turner III 13 and Liam Murphy 11. ----
